		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Bard's Easy way from level 1-35!!</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:gootey@hotmail.com">Eversinger (Dreamlessnotes)</a> | 
		            5/17/2001 1:51:23 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">NOTE:  Lots of this is not actually what i wrote, i coppied it from another guide to tell you a little about bards.  if you have already read this from a different guide, please scroll down to see what i wrote!! Thanks<BR>
<BR>
      Bards&#8230; hmmn the jack of many skills and the master of none. This is true to the extent that we can&#8217;t damage with our songs as much as a wizard or dish the melee damage like a monk or tank like a warrior or heal like a cleric, but we do have something no other class can claim, We CAN do it all and we make everyone around us better.<BR>
My guide will touch on starting race and stats, techniques and tricks, and appropriate fighting areas for certain levels. Of course this is all opinion but I have been successful up to Level 27 doing this.<BR>
The big debate on which race and who has the best stats. I say choose the one you like the look of and how they will interact with other players. The stats between wood elves, half elves, and humans is not so noticeable as to make you choose one just because of stats. I will list stats in order of importance to me. I feel the most important stat is agility. The higher it is the more the mobs miss you and that is ALWAYS a good thing. Strength and charisma are a close second each having an equal importance. As you may know bards can wear plate. Nice. It was intended that way because of the taunting power our songs radiate. Never underestimate Armor Class (AC) when you do get hit this will determine how much damage you take. With that said the higher your strength the more plate you can wear increasing your armor class. Charisma, that is a little more elusive in terms of seeing the effects of a higher number. This really determines how well you can sleep, lull, or charm a mob ( MOB being monsters). In the early levels it is not relevant but later on it sure does make a huge difference in how effective you are in those situations. Dexterity is the last of my four main stats and it is used in determining how well you target a creature for a strike (less misses) and in how often your weapons, the ones that have an effect, produce an effect in battle. Though as of this writing I am hearing more and more that it takes a real good jump in dexterity to produce a small increase in Procs (effects). Stamina, intelligence, and wisdom are all nice to keep high but with such emphasis on the other stats I have maybe a few points because of a side effect of one of my items i.e. Purity belt is +2 strength and ALSO +2 stamina. That is my take. I am a half elf bard because I felt it gave me the best balance of my four main stats. My starting stats Strength 95, stamina 70, agility 95, dexterity 95, wisdom 60, charisma 85, intelligence 75. <BR>
The bard is hands down the hardest character to play effectively. No other character mixes in so many skills and so many different types of songs. Let me explain how songs works. Some songs you can sing continuously i.e. Chant of Battle so every 3-6 seconds the effect will be refreshed or &#8220;PULSE&#8221;. Other songs only play for a one time effect so you have to start the song again i.e Brusco&#8217;s Bellow. There is a tactic called TWISTING where you start a song until it &#8220;pulses&#8221; then stop it and start another song until it pulses to get the effect of both songs. This actually can be done for three songs. So if you twist right you can benefit from the effect of three different songs at the same time. How is that possible you may ask? Most songs after its initial pulse will remain in effect for an additional 2 more pulses. A bard that does not twist is an inefficient bard. Learn to do it early and perfect the practice as you will no doubt be doing this throughout your career. How do I do it? Well the easiest way to do it is to set up hotkeys so you only have to use the keyboard instead of the mouse. If you left click and hold on a song icon while in windowed mode it will attach that spell slot on your cursor. Just drop it on your hotkey bank. Do this for 5 more more songs and dedicate that hot key page for your songs and twist away. <BR>
Twisting, what a great advantage for a bard. It gets better and more difficult. Bard songs sometimes require an instrument in order to play the song, while other songs will have their effects greatly increased if you use the right instrument. Twisting songs is one thing but twisting instruments at the same time to get the best effects can be a real challenge at first. I either use weapons and sing the songs or I twist instruments with songs. I never switch between instruments and weapons in battle. So I call them modes. Weapon mode or instrument mode. Instrument mode is the tricky one. You have to twist your songs as well as twist the instruments appropriate for that song. Again we go back to the hotkey page. Setup a separate page for instrument mode. Hotkey three songs and then hotkey your second melee slot and two inventory slots. Here is an example. Once you reach L18 you get a kick arse DOT song, Denon`s Disruptive Discord. You can sing but it packs a wallop if you use a brass instrument with it. Also Chords of Dissonace works the same way but using a lute increases its damage and of course Hymn of Restoration with a lute heals a lot more. This is my instrument attack setup. I use Hymn, Chords, then Denon&#8217;s I start Hymn with Lute in hand then twist in chords. All this while I have my brass in instrument on my mouse cursor. I twist in Denon&#8217;s and drop my brass horn into my hotkeyed melee slot and I am now using my brass for the Denon effect. I still have my lute on my cursor so I twist back to Hymn and drop my lute in that slot now and repeat the process. After a little practice it gets to be second nature. It pisses off the mobs but oh do you do damage. Ok you are on Twist overload. Lets talk about some tactics that will help to be more efficient in group and solo. In the group setting remember you are not the tank. Let me say that again, YOU ARE NOT THE TANK. Don&#8217;t be afraid to mix it up and take some damage to spread it out but don&#8217;t think you are the point man. In the lower levels this is easy to get used to because everyone is about equal attack and defense wise. Don&#8217;t let that cloud your tactics later on or you will be dying a lot. But there will be times when you are the only one that can tank and in those instances you must. But if there is another hybrid or a warrior amoung you let them be the point man. Before we go any further let me say that you most likely will end up being chewed on more than most because of the power of your songs to effect the whole group and the mobs don&#8217;t like that one bit. Our songs have massive taunting power so be wary. If you find yourself getting pounded quit playing your songs and stop attacking and let the warriors and other hybrids taunt. DON&#8217;T keep attacking and playing a song. In the lower levels Hymn of Restoration is a great group song in battle. The higher you go the more you will notice the mobs do way more damage and that heal song will taunt them like you wont believe so I advise not using it in battle unless you are using the all instrument attack because those songs will taunt anyway might as well heal. We have so many songs with different effects and it would be impossible to explain the tactics of all of them in a group setting. It depends a lot on the group makeup as well as the type of mobs you are fighting. Examples. EX 1 Tank heavy group fighting non casting creatures with a lot of hit points. Twist Anthem de arms, a debuff song to slow the mob&#8217;s attack rate like chain or binding and mix in a bellow and alternate with Jaxon&#8217;s jig of vigor to keep everyone&#8217;s stamina up. Ex 2 multiple mobs no enchanter so you have to sleep them with Lullaby and twist in a bellow then back to lullaby. Don&#8217;t twist 3 when sleeping or don&#8217;t twist at all and keep starting and stopping Lullaby depending on number of mobs. These type of situations you will learn to adapt to and play the right songs at the right time. It takes practice and expect to fail because you will learn the most from what NOT to do.<BR>
Ahh Soloing as a bard. IMPOSSIBLE, not enough hit points, we can&#8217;t melee, so on so on. I am here to tell you it is possible and very effective. I spoke of Instrument mode with those three particular songs, Chords, Denon&#8217;s, and Hymn. Find a spot where you wont attract other mobs and sing away. It is very effective on blues and whites although a bit chancy on yellows. I still solo this way even at L27. Then there is always Kiting. You twist accelerando and bellow. First start with accelerando already on then bellow, then bellow again until it is close. Start to run then start up accelerando again and bellow until you get message out of range. Then stop and continue to bellow until it is in range. Kiting is a LONG process once you start it you can get a feel for how it works. There is another tactic some may say is cheesy, I don&#8217;t think so. If we are able to do it I say go for it. Others say that because they cant do it. First you chain the mob then you fear it and it runs away from you slowly allowing you to hack at it, damage it with song etc. This works best in outdoor areas where the mob has room to run. HEH don&#8217;t do this in dungeon because if the chain breaks he is running for his buddies. Another tactic is the charm. OK set up another hot key page and designate it for charming. Hotkey charm and accelerando and the pet commands /pet attack, and /pet get lost, and /pet guard me. Keep your drum equipped. The charm song has a good range so stay a good distance. Find two unsuspecting victims charm one. If it doesn&#8217;t work charm again until it does. Once charmed target the second one and issue the /pet attack command. Get some distance between you and the mob and sing accelerando in between for two pulses then prepare to charm again. Make sure you target the same one.You cannot Charm a mob that is charmed less you break it, so once charmed you have to wait for it to break for you to re charm. Keep doing this until one is dead hopefully your pet wins. If your pet wins wait for the charm to break the melee it or kite it. I personally don&#8217;t solo a lot I like the group play. <BR>
<BR>
        Okay actually that was a bit of someone elses guide, im here to tell you what I did for levels 1-35--I'm a human from qeynos<BR>
and want to help the people that are stuck on a level lower than 35.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
       Okay levels 1-4  what i did at levels 1 to four is i chased around critters in the newbie grounds such as snake, rat, and bats for level1, then i moved up to firebeatles and all the other low stuff at level 2, at three and four i continued with firebeetles and rats and bats and snakes and gnoll pups (hehe little too many ands there) that didnt take me very long butn with the loot i collected off the firebeetles especially i was able to buy my 4 songsand some cloth armor.<BR>
<BR>
    at level 5 i went to blackburrow entrance in qeynos hills and camped out the gnolls at the giant gnoll head.  i did this until about level 7 then moved up tognoll watchers at level 8 (which can be found in 2 area's, one being around a tree near entrance and another being on the side of the nearest hill.)  i only did those for about 1 level since they were a bit difficult cuz they popped in 3's, at level 9 i headed ytonto BB (blackburrow) and did general low level gnoll until level 10.  I then decided to camp the snakes on the snake ledge <BR>
(can be tricky to get to. i will explain how to get there.  first you enter Blackburrow and walk to then end of the little tunnel, you should be facing out of it and seeing a big bit infront of you,a big hollow tree to the left and some other stuff top the right, head right and follow wall, you should go around a tree and over onto the right part of the pit, continueto hug the wall and you should find yourself at a door soon enough, open the door and head through. watch out for scrawny gnolls and trains. follow the tunnel until you get to a room with a bridge on the right, straight ahead there is another bridge accept this one is pretty long, and to your left there should be a little slope up to the wall.  go right and over the short fat bridge, go down the hill and there shoukld then be a little moat type thing infront oif you, a rock to your rightand you should be abloe to go under the bridge if you go right and a wall on your left, go left and watch out for passing by gnolls, follow the left wall until you get to some water, it should be pretty shallow. walk into the water and go stright, you should fall off a water fall and be in a little pond.  look under the waterfall and you will see that you can go rightunder it.  go under the waterfall and up the ladder, once up there should be giant snakes infront of you and you should see a little platform type thing that rises up like steps.  this is the snake ledge)anyways, i camped snakes until like level 13 (might've had to group a bit)<BR>
<BR>
at level 13 i headed to dervs in WC 9long run from BB)  and did them to about 15, at 15 i went over to oasis (can be accesed from north ro or south ro) and got in an orc group for the orc highway.  i did that until level 16.  <BR>
<BR>
   at levekl 16 i headed all the way over to erudin (yes the zone erudin, not toxxulia forest)  when i entered erudin i looked around for Phloatin Highbrow, an NPC that is about level 18 he is in the bluehawks building.  now dont worry about guards or anything attacking you, no one else in erudin really cares about phloatin.  if you dont mind losing erud citizen faction (which only has 2 citizens, so its not a big deal to lose the faction) then this guy is right for you.   Erudin is filled with pathing bugs so pull phloatin with bellow and look around for a pathing bug (which means the mob (monster) has to go around an obsticle or takes the long way to get to you) so that you can just bellow him, move a bit, he comes a different way at you, belolow, move,and so forth. i did that until level 22, sometimes you can melee him but he can hgit pretty hard.  <BR>
<BR>
at level 22 i went to the millers camp in qeynos<BR>
hills and campedthe millers (almost always someone there taking a miller) there are 2 millers.  the millers are level 25 but are very easy to kite, at level 23 we get our snare song so i just got the help of a nearby druid for snare. you can train them way back to the end of the zone, and if thier still not dead, go back the otherway in the direction of the camp, keep this preogress up and learn to twist songs!! selo's, chain and bellow works pretty well and since chain and bellow is sing, you only have to have 1 instrooment out, your drum.   I did miller until level 35 (yes i know, 13 levels of the same thing, ICK) but it goes by pretty fast since thier AWSOME experience at your level!!  they grow easier with time and drop some nice loot.   the loot is...<BR>
<BR>
Baobob miller-Fine steel scimitar (always) money (always) can drop up to 5 plat (platinum) and the ocasional words or rune.<BR>
<BR>
Chanda Miller- rusty dagger, bronze short sword (always) money (always) can drop the same amount of money as Baobob does and the ocasianal rune or words.<BR>
<BR>
be aware that if you are sharing camp, always try to take baobob.. even though he has like 200more hp, his MR (magik resistance) is MUCH lower than chanda's plus he has a better loot.   IT'S BETTER TO BE SAFE THAN SORRY!!!!  <BR>
<BR>
      1 last thing, if someone is camping both millers say that he/she needs to share one =)  i got someone sent to the zone &quot;Arena&quot; for not sharing with me. just petition if they dont share hehe.. long live GM's! Hope all this helped! <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
      Well thats all i have to say about bards for now! goodluck and may the force, err, tune be with you!<BR>
<BR>
Eversinger (Dreamlessnotes)<BR>
Bristlebane<BR>

